     </m:mrow>
     <m:mrow>
        <m:mfrac>
        <m:mn> 1 </m:mn>
        <m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
        </m:mfrac>
     </m:mrow>
     </m:msup>


   </m:mtd>
 </m:mtr>


</m:mtable>
</m:mstyle> 
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-60">We observe here that resultant vector lies in the plane formed by the two component vectors being added. The resultant vector is, therefore, perpendicular to third component vector. Thus, the magnitude of the sum of vector (
